.TH "__ssp_receive_char" 9 "__ssp_receive_char" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__ssp_receive_char \- receive a byte from the UART
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char" __ssp_receive_char
.BI "(struct sifive_serial_port *ssp "  ","
.BI "char *is_empty "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ssp" 12
pointer to a struct sifive_serial_port
.IP "is_empty" 12
char pointer to return whether the RX FIFO is empty
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Try to read a byte from the SiFive UART RX FIFO, referenced by
\fIssp\fP, and to return it.  Also returns the RX FIFO empty bit in
the char pointed to by \fIch\fP.  The caller must pass the byte back to the
Linux serial layer if needed.
.SH "RETURN"
the byte read from the UART RX FIFO.
